The paper is about automated program repair techniques, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper specifically focuses on a syntactic search-based approach for program repair, which involves searching for and reusing existing code fragments, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also proposes a new repair technique, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the techniques on bug datasets, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
